<subSubSection pageId="11" pageNumber="12" type="remarks">
<paragraph pageId="11" pageNumber="12">Remarks.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="11" pageNumber="12">
<taxonomicName class="Gastropoda" family="Hydrobiidae" genus="Pseudoislamia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Pseudoislamia balcanica" order="Littorinimorpha" pageId="11" pageNumber="12" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="balcanica">Pseudoislamia balcanica</taxonomicName>
is an endemic species previously known only from its type locality, the NE rocky banks of Lake Trichonis near Myrtia (
<bibRefCitation author="Radoman, P" journalOrPublisher="Department of Sciences" pageId="18" pageNumber="19" title="Hydrobioidea, a Superfamily of Prosobranchia (Gastropoda)" volumeTitle="Monographs DXLVII" year="1983">Radoman 1983</bibRefCitation>
). 
<bibRefCitation author="Szarowska, M" journalOrPublisher="Folia Malacologica" pageId="18" pageNumber="19" pagination="99 - 168" title="Molecular phylogeny, systematics and morphological character evolution in the balkan Rissooidea (Caenogastropoda)." volume="14" year="2006">Szarowska (2006)</bibRefCitation>
considers this species to be extinct. In 2007 and 2008, two small populations were found near Myrtia by 
<bibRefCitation author="Albrecht, C" journalOrPublisher="Malacologia" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" pagination="357 - 375" title="Mollusc biodiversity and endemism in the potential ancient Lake Trichonis, Greece." url="10.4002/040.051.0209" volume="51" year="2009">Albrecht et al. (2009)</bibRefCitation>
. Our sampling revealed that although 
<taxonomicName class="Gastropoda" family="Hydrobiidae" genus="Pseudoislamia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Pseudoislamia balcanica" order="Littorinimorpha" pageId="11" pageNumber="12" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="balcanica">Pseudoislamia balcanica</taxonomicName>
forms small sized populations,it is more widespread than previously thought and thrives both in lentic and lotic waters.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
